# config/.env — used by `docker compose` for variable interpolation.
# Copy this file to `config/.env` and fill in the real values.
# File permissions: chmod 600
#
# NOTE: This is a SEPARATE file from .env_llm and .env_proxy because Docker Compose
# variable interpolation and env_file mechanism are different:
#   - This file is auto-loaded by Compose for ${VAR} substitution.
#   - .env_llm / .env_proxy are passed into the container via `env_file:` directive
#     and exposed to the SearXNG process as environment variables.
# We deliberately keep SEARXNG_SECRET here (not in .env_llm) so the secret is
# scoped to the Compose stack and is never used by the LLM verifier.

# Generate with: python3 -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"
SEARXNG_SECRET=replace_with_secrets_token_hex_64_chars

# Optional: override path to settings.yml. Default is ./settings.yml next to docker-compose.yml.
# SEARXNG_SETTINGS_PATH=./settings.yml
